      "Hello @cicku \r\n\r\nI recently tried to build on Fedora and wrote instructions for it, but they haven't been pushed yet (it's coming soon). Here they are\r\n\r\n-----------------------\r\n_Note_: There currently is a bug in the file `external/protobuf-plugin-closure/Makefile`.\r\nThe directory `/usr/lib` is hardcoded and if you run on Fedora 64 bits, you will have to replace it with `/usr/lib64`.\r\nSee [https://github.com/rethinkdb/rethinkdb/issues/853](https://github.com/rethinkdb/rethinkdb/issues/853) to track progress.\r\n\r\nThese instructions were tested on Fedora 18.\r\n\r\n#### Install build dependencies ####\r\nInstall the main dependencies.\r\n\r\n```\r\nsudo yum install gcc-c++ protobuf-compiler protobuf-c protobuf-c-devel protobuf-devel boost-devel openssl-devel v8-devel gperftools-devel nodejs npm curl ctags-etags m4 protobuf-static boost-static git-core python-pip\r\n```\r\n\r\nInstall some node dependencies.\r\n\r\n```\r\nsudo npm install -g coffee-script less handlebars\r\n```\r\n\r\nInstall Pyyaml\r\n\r\n```\r\nsudo python-pip install pyyaml\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Get the source code ####\r\nClone the RethinkDB repository.\r\n\r\n```\r\ngit clone --depth 1 https://github.com/rethinkdb/rethinkdb.git\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Build RethinkDB ####\r\nBuilding with tcmalloc raises some issue, we add the flag `--without-tcmalloc`.\r\n\r\n```\r\n./configure --without-tcmalloc\r\nmake\r\n```"
